    "finalText": "I can’t give you a trustworthy “cash we can touch today” number right now because the live Acumatica cash-position pull failed.\n\nWhat I do know:\n- The **live ERP source** for cash movement is currently unavailable.\n- The failure happened on the **AP checks/outflow side**, so any net cash number I gave you would be incomplete and potentially wrong.\n\nWhat that means:\n- I can’t confirm **actual available cash today** from the accounting system of record.\n- Anything else would be a guess, and this is exactly the kind of number that shouldn’t be guessed.\n\nWhat to do next:\n1. **Retry the cash position report** once the Acumatica endpoint is stable.\n2. If you need an immediate operating read, pull:\n   - current bank balance,\n   - today’s expected deposits,\n   - today’s checks/ACH hitting,\n   - payroll timing,\n   - and any restricted cash exclusions.\n3. If you want, I can also check **AR aging** and **AP aging** right now to show:\n   - what should be collectible soon,\n   - what needs to go out,\n   - and where the near-term pressure is.\n\nIf you want, I’ll run **AR aging + AP aging** next and give you the best practical same-day cash read despite the ERP cash report being down."
  },
